# Accessibility (a11y) Guidelines

- Use semantic HTML elements for structure and meaning.
- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible.
- Provide visible focus indicators for keyboard navigation.
- Use ARIA labels and roles only when necessary.
- Ensure sufficient color contrast (WCAG AA/AAA).
- Provide meaningful alt text for images.
- Caption videos and transcribe audio content.
- Label all form fields clearly.
- Clearly indicate errors and how to fix them.
- Use ARIA live regions for dynamic content updates.
